.SH NAME
WebGLRenderingContext.generateMipmap \- WebGLRenderingContext:
generateMipmap() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]WebGLRenderingContext.generateMipmap()\f[B]\f[R] method
of the WebGL API generates a set of mipmaps for a
\f[CR]WebGLTexture\f[R] object.
.PP
Mipmaps are used to create distance with objects.
A higher\-resolution mipmap is used for objects that are closer, and a
lower\-resolution mipmap is used for objects that are farther away.
It starts with the resolution of the texture image and halves the
resolution until a 1x1 dimension texture image is created.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
generateMipmap(target)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]target\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the binding point (target) of the active
texture whose mipmaps will be generated.
Possible values:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_2D\f[R]: A two\-dimensional texture.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP\f[R]: A cube\-mapped texture.
.PP
When using a WebGL 2 context, the following values are available
additionally:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_3D\f[R]: A three\-dimensional texture.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY\f[R]: A two\-dimensional array texture.
.RE
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
gl.generateMipmap(gl.TEXTURE_2D);
.EE
